<para id="import-auto-id2766839">Children in peripheral nations have little to no daily access to computers and the Internet, while children in core nations are constantly exposed to this technology. This is an example of:</para><list id="fs-id1492212" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>the digital divide</item>
<item>human ecology</item>
<item>modernization theory</item>
<item>dependency theory</item>
</list>
</problem>
<solution id="eip-id1169762446162">
<label/>
<para id="eip-id1169762334505">A</para>
</solution>                </exercise><exercise id="fs-id1909276" type="section-quiz"><problem id="fs-id1969428">
<para id="import-auto-id1961492">When sociologists think about technology as an agent of social change, which of the following is <emphasis effect="italics">not</emphasis> an example?</para>
